Constructor
Initializes the Calculator object with result and mem set to 0.0.

add()
Prompts the user to enter two numbers (or "result"/"mem").

Adds the two values.

Stores and prints the result.

subtract()
Prompts the user to enter two numbers (or "result"/"mem").

Subtracts the second number from the first.

Stores and prints the result.

multiply()
Prompts the user to enter two numbers (or "result"/"mem").

Multiplies the two numbers.

Stores and prints the result.

divide()
Prompts the user to enter two numbers (or "result"/"mem").

Divides the first number by the second.

Stores and prints the result.

Note: Does not explicitly handle division by zero.

square()
Prompts the user for one number (or "result"/"mem").

Squares the number.

Stores and prints the result.

sqrt()
Prompts the user for one number (or "result"/"mem").

Calculates the square root.

Stores and prints the result.

Assumes the input is non-negative (no error handling for negative input).

setMem()
Prompts the user for a number (or "result").

Stores the value in memory (mem).

Prints the memory value.

printMem()
Prints the current stored memory value.

parseInput(const std::string& input)
Converts the input string to a double.

If input is "result", returns the last result.

If input is "mem", returns the memory value.

Otherwise converts the string to a double using std::stod.

welcome()
Prints a prompt listing available operations.

parseOperation(const std::string& input)
Takes a string representing an operation.

Calls the corresponding function based on input, e.g. "+", "add", "sqrt", "setmem".

Supports multiple synonyms for each operation.

Does nothing if the input does not match any operation.

